Snow Plow Sam 1 Classes are for skaters 3-5 years old.                                                             

Curriculum Highlights:  Sit & Stand up, march, glide on 2 feet, dip in place  

Class is 25 minutes in length.

Be sure to wear a helmet (a bike helmet that fits well is acceptable)

Please note that markers are used during classes to draw on the ice.  Clothing may get marked up if a skater falls, please keep this in mind when dressing your skaters.  Dark clothing or clothing that is not of concern if it should get marker on them.

*Pre-Registration Required.  Walk up space is not likely/available.

*Be sure to obtain/renew membership at www.learntoskateusa.com - required at registration with XIC

attributes.name: Learn to Skate - WINTER 2026 (3-5yr Group Classes)
attributes.description:
Preschool aged Class Options (3-5 yr old)  /   Preschool Learn to Skate Options

"WINTER 2026 SEMESTER"

Tot/Preschool Class Options:

First time 3yr, 4yr, 5yr old skater should consider:  Snowplow Sam 1 class on class days with various other ages/levels offered.  (Mon, Tues, Sat options)   or   consider...

Preschool Class/Ice Explorer on Thursdays at approx 1:05-1:30pm //  This class is intended for tots to attend class at a time of day that is more quiet and less intimidating for our youngest skaters starting out.

Continuuing 3yr, 4yr, 5yr old skaters that have completed their first class with us -  should consider the Instructor Recommended next level.  (Class day options include:  Mondays, Tuesdays, Wednesdays (preschool specific), Thursday, or Saturdays)


All Snowplow Sam Classes are Upbeat, interactive, utilizing props to assist in developing fundamentals of skating skills.

Classes Require membership with www.learntoskateusa.com

PRE-REGISTRATION IS REQUIRED!!!

NO OTHER DISCOUNTS APPLY

NOTE:  Skaters 3-5 yrs old - that are very new or timid and require even a little more attention to get started would qualify for "Ice Explorers".
Contact Skating Director, Jenny Gwyn jennyg@xicenter.com to explore additional options or pending classes that may be elgible to be added to the curriculum.
